origination.label: Creator
origination.corpname: University of California, Los Angeles. Office of the Chancellor

did.abstract: Record Series 549 contains the administrative files of UCLA Chancellor Charles E. Young, generated primarily between 1968-1997.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. All requests to access special collections materials must be made in advance using the request button located on this page.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Reproduction and Use
userestrict.p: Copyright to portions of this collection has been assigned to the UCLA Library Special Collections. The library can grant permission to publish for materials to which it holds the copyright. Commercial use may require additional rights that must be determined and obtained by the researcher. All requests for copyright permission to publish must be submitted in writing to Library Special Collections. Credit shall be given as follows: The Regents of the University of California on behalf of the UCLA Library Special Collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Office of the Chancellor. Administrative files of Charles E. Young (University Archives Record Series 594). UCLA Library Special Collections, University Archives, University of California, Los Angeles.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Record Series 594 was received in 2005 and 2008 from the UCLA Chancellor's Communications Services (CCS).

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Record Series 594 was processed by the staff of the Chancellor's Communication Services (CCS) prior to transfer to the UCLA University Archives. The original Container List (MsAccess database) was created by CCS staff under the direction of the UCLA University Archives.

We are committed to providing ethical, inclusive, and anti-racist description of the materials we steward, and to remediating existing description of our materials that contains language that may be offensive or cause harm. We invite you to submit feedback about how our collections are described, and how they could be described more accurately, by filling out the form located on our website: Report Potentially Offensive Description in Library Special Collections.

bioghist.head: Biographical History
bioghist.p: Charles E. Young served as UCLA's fourth Chancellor from 1968-1997.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Record Series 549 contains the administrative files of UCLA Chancellor Charles E. Young. Files regard Instructional Units; Academic and Staff Personnel; Universitywide Administration; Board of Regents; Campus Administration; Public Service; Spch. Campus Administration; Extramural Support; Systemwide Administration; Campus Management; Student Services and Activities; Organized Research and Museums; Intramural Relations; Instructional Support Units; Chancellor's Advisory Committee on the Status of Women; University Policies Commission; Governmental Relations; Public relations; LA Division Academic Senate; Student Associations; Plant Development and Maintenance; Instruction; Museum of Cultural History; Graduate School of Education; Academic Senate; Public Ceremonies; Museums and Special Collections; University of California Campuses; Campus Human Resources; and Extended University.
This is an inactive record series; no additional University records are expected to be added.
